# Introduction to Backend (Flask)

# Project Overview
This project demonstrates the basics of backend development using Flask.  
It includes installing Flask, creating a simple backend application, running a local server, and displaying a welcome message in the browser.

# Objectives Covered
- Install Flask
- Create a basic Flask project
- Run a local development server
- Render an HTML template
- Display a welcome message in the browser

# Project Structure
Feb_W4_Day1/
- app.py
- templates/
  - index.html
- README.md

# Technologies Used
- Python
- Flask
- HTML
- CSS (basic styling)

# How to Install Flask
Open terminal and run:
pip install flask

# How to Run the Project
1. Open the project folder in VS Code.
2. Open terminal inside the folder.
3. Run: python app.py
4. Open browser and go to:
   http://127.0.0.1:5000

# Expected Output
A welcome page displayed in the browser served by Flask backend.

# Learning Outcome
- Understanding of backend basics
- Running a local server
- Using routes in Flask
- Rendering templates from backend
- Connecting backend with frontend

